%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-3.4-ea.2/batch-gateway.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant API as API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Redis as Redis<br/>6379/TCP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Processor as Batch Processor<br/>9090/TCP
    participant Gateway as Inference Gateway<br/>(llm-d / GAIE)

    Note over Client,Gateway: Flow 1: File Upload
    Client->>API: POST /v1/files (multipart)<br/>X-MaaS-User: tenant-id
    API->>S3: Upload JSONL file<br/>TLS 1.2+ / AWS credentials
    S3-->>API: Upload confirmation
    API->>Redis: Store file metadata<br/>Optional TLS / Password
    Redis-->>API: OK
    API-->>Client: File object (file_id)

    Note over Client,Gateway: Flow 2: Batch Job Submission
    Client->>API: POST /v1/batches<br/>X-MaaS-User: tenant-id<br/>{"input_file_id": "file_id"}
    API->>Redis: Create batch metadata<br/>Optional TLS / Password
    API->>Redis: Enqueue to priority queue
    Redis-->>API: OK
    API-->>Client: Batch object (batch_id, status: validating)

    Note over Client,Gateway: Flow 3: Async Batch Processing
    Processor->>Redis: Poll priority queue<br/>BZPOPMIN (blocking)
    Redis-->>Processor: Job payload
    Processor->>Redis: Get batch metadata
    Redis-->>Processor: Batch details (input_file_id, model)
    Processor->>S3: Download input JSONL file<br/>TLS 1.2+ / AWS credentials
    S3-->>Processor: JSONL content

    loop For each request in JSONL
        Processor->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>TLS 1.2+ / mTLS<br/>Bearer Token (optional)
        Gateway-->>Processor: Inference response
        Processor->>Redis: Update progress status
    end

    Processor->>S3: Upload output JSONL file<br/>TLS 1.2+ / AWS credentials
    Processor->>Redis: Update batch status: completed

    Note over Client,Gateway: Flow 4: Batch Cancellation
    Client->>API: POST /v1/batches/{id}/cancel<br/>X-MaaS-User: tenant-id
    API->>Redis: Remove from priority queue
    API->>Redis: Publish cancel event (channel)
    Redis-->>Processor: Cancel event notification
    Processor->>Redis: Update batch status: cancelled
    API-->>Client: Batch object (status: cancelling)
